    <note>Feng(4) Mi [27094] He changed his mingzi from Yanlu and was younger brother of the Southern Tang Zaixiang, Yenji [3316]. He also served the Southern Tang and was granted lands by Song Taizu in 962 when Southern Tang submitted and he died shortly thereafter. These lands were apparently located in Ming Zhou, Cixi Xian. See documentation for Feng(4) Zhun [20509]. NanTang shu, 11.3a-5a. CBD, 4, 3748.</note>
